Therefore the bandwidth shown (#Requests * (scaleFactor) / time) may be higher than actual bandwidth (#Requests includes every read & write request).

Note: Incorrect PEP constraints may prevent devices from entering D3. Use Intel PEP Checker to review constraint issues if device is not entering D3 as expected.

Note: D3Unknown time occurs when a device has entered D3 prior to starting a SoC Watch collection. This occurs because the collection does not capture the event needed to distinguish D3Cold from D3Hot so this time is labeled D3Unknown instead.

Note: Some devices may display D3Hot instead of D3Cold or vice versa. To be certain check the PCIe LPM Summary table (-f pcie-lpm) if link is in L2/L3/Down state then device is in D3Cold and if link is in L1.1/L1.2 state then the device is in D3Hot.
